Description: St Antony tormented by devils, after Schongauer; the saint is in mid-air, surrounded by eight devils. Etching
Curator's comments: Lehrs notes that the monograms and the date 1530 are false, and the print probably dates from the eighteenth century. The title underneath 'A. Anthonius' has been trimmed away.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / German engravings, etchings and woodcuts c.1400-1700 (54g) (After Raphael de Mey after Schongauer)
Lehrs 1908-34 / Geschichte und kritische Katalog des deutschen, niederländischen und französischen Kupferstichs im XV Jahrhundert (V.250.54g)
Associated names: Representation of: St Antony of Egypt
